<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00731</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING REPUBLIC ACT NO. 7653, ENTITLED "THE NEW CENTRAL BANK ACT"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seek to enhance the administration of the monetary credit and banking system of the Republic by among other things, affirming the authority of the Bangko Sentral to administer the payments and settlements systems; proposed that the authority of the examiners to access deposit accounts which was granted before and was exercised without abuse, be restored; BSP officials and personnel should be granted the same legal protection given to the PDIC under R.A. No. 9576.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NOGRALES, KARLO ALEXEI B., NOGRALES, JERICHO JONAS B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Economic</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (048 2016-11-23)</td><td>2. Macapagal Arroyo (048 2016-11-23)</td><tr><td>3. Cortuna (048 2016-11-23)</td><td>4. Ferrer J. (048 2016-11-23)</td><tr><td>5. Ong (H.) (048 2016-11-23)</td><td>6. Salon (048 2016-11-23)</td><tr><td>7. Limkaichong (048 2016-11-23)</td><td>8. Almonte (048 2016-11-23)</td><tr><td>9. Turabin-Hataman (048 2016-11-23)</td><td>10. Villarin (048 2016-11-23)</td><tr><td>11. Caminero (048 2016-11-23)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Deliberated upon by the Mother Committee on 2016-11-22</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-1st meeting.  Approved without further discussion as per Sec. 48 of the Rules of the House, in consolidation with HBs 2436, 3456 & 4283.  Approval carried with it the proposal of Rep. Macapagal-Arroyo to insert the provision prohibiting the BSP from supervising the operations of AMLA.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Scheduled for meeting/hearing on 2017-10-11</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp3. Approved by the Committee on Appropriations on 2017-10-11</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Unnumbered Sustitute Bill was approved with amendments.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp4. Committee Report approved on 2017-11-28</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Draft Substitute bill approved containing the amendments introduced by the Appropriations and Ways & Means committees</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp5. Committee Report filed on 2018-02-28</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-CR 637 HB 7296 Substitute bill for HBs 731, 2436, 4283, & 6599</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp6. Recommended recommitment to the committee of referral on 2018-03-18</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Committee on Rules recommitted to mother committee substitute bill HB 7296 under CR 637.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp7. Deliberated upon by the Mother Committee on 2018-03-20</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Approved amendment  raised by the Committee on Rules on substitute bill HB 7296 under CR 637.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp8. Committee Report filed on 2018-05-21</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Committee Report 741
